+{"id":"xf-11.1.2","title":"Implement DM context display in cmd_search","description":"## Goal

Remove the 'not implemented' error and implement proper DM context display when --context flag is used with DM search.

## Current Code (main.rs lines 286-288)

```rust
if args.context {
    anyhow::bail\!("DM context output is not implemented yet.");
}
```

## Implementation

Replace the bail\! with actual context handling logic. The implementation should:

1. **Detect when context applies**: Only when --types includes 'dm' and --context is set

2. **Extract conversation_id from results**: Each DM search result's metadata JSON contains conversation_id

3. **Fetch conversation context**: Use the new get_conversation_messages method

4. **Display with highlighting**: Show full conversation with the matched message highlighted

## Pseudocode

```rust
// In cmd_search, after getting search results:
if args.context && args.types.as_ref().map_or(false, |t| t.iter().any(|x| matches\!(x, DataType::Dm))) {
    // Group results by conversation_id
    let mut conversations_shown: HashSet<String> = HashSet::new();

    for result in &results {
        if result.result_type \!= SearchResultType::DirectMessage {
            continue;
        }

        // Extract conversation_id from metadata
        let conv_id = result.metadata["conversation_id"].as_str().unwrap_or_default();

        // Skip if we already showed this conversation
        if conversations_shown.contains(conv_id) {
            continue;
        }
        conversations_shown.insert(conv_id.to_string());

        // Fetch full conversation
        let messages = storage.get_conversation_messages(conv_id)?;

        // Find matched message IDs in this conversation
        let matched_ids: HashSet<_> = results.iter()
            .filter(|r| r.metadata["conversation_id"].as_str() == Some(conv_id))
            .map(|r| r.id.as_str())
            .collect();

        // Display conversation with highlights
        display_dm_conversation(&messages, &matched_ids, &cli.format);
    }
} else {
    // Normal result display
    for result in &results {
        print_result(&result, &cli.format, ...);
    }
}
```

## Display Format (text mode)

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Conversation (2023-12-15)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  [14:32] 12345678: Hey, want to grab dinner?
► [14:35] 87654321: Sure\! When were you thinking?
  [14:36] 12345678: How about 7pm?
  [14:40] 87654321: Perfect, see you then
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```

The ► indicates matched messages, and the line should be colored (cyan or yellow).

## Edge Cases

1. **No DM types in search**: If --context is used without --types dm, show warning or ignore
2. **Multiple matches in conversation**: Show conversation once with all matches highlighted
3. **Empty conversations**: Skip display
4. **Very long conversations**: Consider limiting to N messages around matches

## Dependencies

- xf-11.1.1: get_conversation_messages must exist first

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] --context no longer throws 'not implemented' error
- [ ] DM results show full conversation context
- [ ] Matched messages are visually highlighted
- [ ] Conversations are deduplicated (shown once even if multiple matches)
- [ ] Works with all output formats (text, json, compact, csv)","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-10T19:05:01.194389-05:00","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-01-10T19:05:01.194389-05:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"xf-11.1.2","depends_on_id":"xf-11.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},{"issue_id":"xf-11.1.2","depends_on_id":"xf-11.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"}]}
